{"type":"message","id":"a77c68be","parentId":"a894597f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:08:27.551Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the pulse log while also waiting for the script to finish.","thinkingSignature":"3c965515db7680072ed910fca33c245ed2d602b663004b031a6d80a595bfab9a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f7bgitu4efmx_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 150714.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f7bgitu4efmx_2","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"glow-dune","timeout":60000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":411,"output":112,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12768,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774379304713}}
{"type":"message","id":"99c03600","parentId":"a77c68be","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:08:27.561Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_f7bgitu4efmx_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 150714\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/HYBRID_CFI_FREQ_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and the next action needed.\r\n\r\nFrom the goals:\r\n- Phase 1 Advancement: CFI Compression Experiment was completed\r\n- Key insight: Need THREE-DIMENSIONAL filter - CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n- Next experiment: Hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring vs binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThe pending action is:\r\n- [ ] Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n  - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n  - Test: does this distinguish \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)?\r\n  - Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThis is the next concrete action. I need to implement this hybrid scoring experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist that I can build upon. The CFI compression synthesis document mentioned running experiments with 200 pulses and 80/20 split. I should create a script or analysis that implements the hybrid scoring formula and tests it against the binary thresholds.\r\n\r\nThe formula to test:\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThis should:\r\n- Score constant format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1) = 1 × min(1, 160/120) = 1 × 1 = 1.0 (still high!)\r\n- Score research trajectory (freq=60, CFI=0.7) = 0.7 × min(1, 60/120) = 0.7 × 0.5 = 0.35\r\n\r\nHmm, that's not quite right. The constant format would still score high. Let me reconsider.\r\n\r\nActually wait - the insight was that freq=160 with CFI=1 is constant format (zero information), but freq=136 with CFI=0.96 is research trajectory. \r\n\r\nI need to rethink the scoring approach. The key is distinguishing between tokens that are truly informative versus those that are merely consistent. The frequency cap alone doesn't solve this - I need a way to down-weight tokens that appear too consistently across pulses. A logarithmic or inverse frequency component might better capture the novelty aspect I'm looking for.\r\n\r\nThe core insight is that high CFI tokens with extreme frequency (like 160) are format artifacts, not useful signals. I should test a few scoring variants: capping frequency contribution, penalizing very high frequencies, or using a sigmoid-like function that peaks at moderate frequencies. Let me implement these experiments to see which approach actually separates research trajectory from noise.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Synthesis revealed that binary thresholds fail because constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.0) score identically to research trajectory tokens (freq=136, CFI=0.96). A multiplicative scoring approach is needed to distinguish them.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nDesign and plan the hybrid scoring experiment (Strategy C) that will test whether score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq/120) can distinguish constant-format from research-trajectory tokens. Create the experimental design document.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: ## Pending\r\n- [ ] Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n  - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n  - Test: does this distinguish \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)?\r\n  - Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n- [ ] Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n- [ ] Design actual compression network (currently only analyzed text invariants)\r\nnew_text: ## Pending\r\n- [ ] Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n- [ ] Design actual compression network (currently only analyzed text invariants)\r\n\r\n## In Progress\r\n### Strategy C: Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\n- **Formula candidates to test:**\r\n  - A: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)  [cap at 120]\r\n  - B: score(T) = CFI(T) × log(freq(T)+1)/log(121)  [diminishing returns]\r\n  - C: score(T) = CFI(T) if freq < 100 else CFI(T) × 0.5  [penalty above 100]\r\n- **Key question:** Does any formula distinguish constant-format (freq=160, CFI=1.0) from research trajectory (freq=136, CFI=0.96)?\r\n- **Expected outcome:** All formulas still score constant-format high - need NEW signal\r\n- **Real insight:** Constant-format tokens have CFI=1.0 EXACTLY - true causal tokens have CFI < 0.99\r\n- **Revised formula:** score(T) = (CFI(T) < 0.99) × CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\nfile: state/goals.md\r\n`\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:07:36\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774379307560}}
