{"type":"message","id":"70b9c02d","parentId":"2cca56f8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:08:47.981Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse ran successfully. Let me summarize the key points from this pulse cycle.\n\nKey events:\n1. The CFI Compression Synthesis was completed\n2. A key insight was found: binary thresholds fail because constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.0) score identically to research trajectory tokens (freq=136, CFI=0.96)\n3. A revised formula was proposed: score(T) = (CFI(T) < 0.99) × CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\n4. One mutation was proposed (the hybrid scoring experiment), and the previous binary threshold experiment was rejected\n\n\n5. The new proposed mutation was created as a new file and committed to the repository\n\nNow I'm looking at the next pulse log to see how the situation evolved.","thinkingSignature":"84b6d2efe0190b97c53855728b7ace050ff97a3cf9aec5060417f5c073887f80"},{"type":"text","text":"**Sandbox Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 15:08**\n\n**What happened:**\n- Completed CFI Compression Synthesis — found that binary CFI/Freq thresholds fail because \"constant format\" tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.0) score identically to \"research trajectory\" tokens (freq=136, CFI=0.96)\n- Proposed a revised hybrid formula: `score(T) = (CFI(T) < 0.99) × CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` — using the exact CFI=1.0 as the filter to remove metaprogramming contamination\n- The previous binary threshold mutation was **rejected**; the new hybrid scoring experiment was **proposed** and committed\n- 6 files changed, 288 insertions, 56 deletions\n\n**Key insight this cycle:** CFI=1.0 exactly is the signal for \"constant format\" (zero information) — real tokens have CFI < 0.99. The frequency cap alone can't distinguish them."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1927,"output":389,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14561,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRea